The speaker, Andrej, is explaining that ChatGPT, an artificial intelligence system, creates a variety of answers based on whatever text-based tasks it is given. For instance, when asked twice to write a haiku about the importance of understanding AI for improving the world, it generated distinctly different responses. This demonstrates its probabilistic nature, or the ability to provide multiple results for one request. Furthermore, he shares that people have used it to generate humorous and unexpected outcomes, and these are cataloged on several websites.